para_trans: On the constitution of a committee headed by the Additional Chief Secretary (Appeals and Security) to study the availability of screens for Marathi films in multiplexes and other difficulties.
Government Decision No: BCR-0825 / Q.No.91 / VISA-5
Main Building, 2nd Floor, Madame Cama Road,

Read: 1) Government Order No. BCR / 6563/53483 SVI, dated 06.03.1968 2) Government Circular No. BCR 532002/26 VISA-5, dated 14.06.2002 3) Ma. The minutes of the meeting held under the chairmanship of the Deputy Chief Minister, Urban Development, Housing and Public Works Department (UH & PWD) dated 05.08.2025.
Introduction: Marathi film releases, like Hindi films in the state of Maharashtra, need to be positively responded to.
So that the Marathi film business will continue smoothly. Marathi films must be extensively advertised before their release.
It is necessary to try how the audience will be attracted to Marathi films. Hence, Marathi in multiplexes.
Additional Chief Secretary (Appeals and Security), Home, to study other difficulties in getting screens for films.
The formation of a committee under the chairmanship of the department was under the consideration of the government.
Government Decision - Additional Head to Study Other Challenges in Getting Screens for Marathi Films in Multiplexes
The committee is being constituted under the chairmanship of Secretary (Appeals and Security), Home Department. The composition of the committee

para_trans: The aforesaid Committee shall submit its report to the Government within 45 days.
The Government decision was made available on the Government of Maharashtra website www.maharashtra.gov.in.
